ts small diagonal, which is the right object to consider in order to understand the ring structure on Chow groups and cohomology. An exploration of a sampling of recent works by Voisin looks at the relation, conjectured in general by Bloch and Beilinson, between the coniveau of general complete intersections and their Chow groups and a very particular property satisfied by the Chow ring of K3 surfaces and conjecturally by hyper-Kähler manifolds. In particular, the book delves into arguments originating in Nori's work that have been further developed by others.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aAlgebraic varieties. 0aDecomposition (Mathematics). 0aHomology theory. 7aMATHEMATICS / Topology.2bisacsh  aBloch-Beilinson conjectures.  aCalabiЙau hypersurfaces.  aChow groups.  aHodge classes.  aHodge coniveau.  aHodge structures.  aK3 surfaces.  aLefschetz standard conjecture.  aMumford's theorem.  aZ-coefficients.  aabelian varieties.  abirational invariants.  acohomology.  acomplex algebraic varieties.  aconiveau.  acycle classes.  adecomposition isomorphism.  adecomposition.  adense Zariski open set.  adiagonal.  afunctoriality.  ageneralized Bloch conjecture.  ageneralized Hodge conjecture.  ageometric coniveau.  ahyper-Khler manifolds.  aintegral coefficients.  aintegral cohomological decomposition.  amixed Hodge structures.  aprojective space.  arational equivalence.  asmall diagonal.  asmooth projective varieties.  aspreading principle.  atorsion coefficients.  atranscendental cohomology.  aunramified cohomology.  avariety.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Annals of Mathematics eBook-Package 1940-2020z9783110494914oZDB-23-PMB08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-